# Mobile internal-beta — the daily win-to-leaderboard path a friend follows on
# their phone: a defused daily run -> /bombsquad/result celebration (rank-
# reveal-first, no modal) -> a signed-in run auto-submits under the account name
# (ruling B), asking once inline which AI helped when the tool is not inferable
# -> /leaderboard ranking. Daily mode is used deliberately so the auto-submit and
# the leaderboard segment are exercised.
#
# Restructured for the e2e harness: each scenario carries a per-scenario
# flow-source comment tracing to e2e/flow-inventory.yaml plus a consumption-layer
# tag, and absolute URLs are normalized to relative paths. The original file's
# landing-overflow, modal, play-through, and recap-copy scenarios were merged
# into the landing-to-daily / home-anonymous-hero / result-to-recap scenarios in
# their own files; what remains here is the daily-win-to-leaderboard flow (the
# "result nickname prompt" + "result to leaderboard row" scenarios merged into
# one journey).
#
# Aligned with the Atlas BombSquad redesign: the result-page module breakdown is
# a per-module panel, not an HTML table, the global rank shows in a rank card
# rather than a "全球排名：#N" line, and the leaderboard is reached through the
# BombSquad landing page (回主页 → 排行榜) rather than a direct result-page link.

Feature: Mobile internal-beta daily win to leaderboard
  As a friend who received the BombSquad link in a group chat
  I want to defuse the daily bomb on my phone, submit my nickname, and see my
  rank on the leaderboard
  So that I finish a full daily run without hitting a layout or navigation break

  Background:
    Given my viewport width is 375 pixels
    And I open /

  # Source: daily-win-to-leaderboard
  @playwright
  Scenario: A first daily win celebrates first, then auto-submits under my name and shows my leaderboard row
    Given I am signed in with the leaderboard name "E2ERunner"
    And I have just defused the bomb in a daily run and the result page is open
    And no leaderboard AI metadata is stored on this device
    Then I see the heading "拆弹成功"
    And I see the total run time
    And the module breakdown lists all 4 modules without horizontal overflow
    And the result page asks which AI I played with

    When I pick AI assistant "Claude" in the settlement
    Then the result page shows my global rank
    And the leaderboard submission carries a plausible time

    When I tap "回主页"
    Then I am back on the BombSquad landing page
    When I tap "排行榜"
    Then the URL path is /leaderboard
    And I see the heading "排行榜"
    And the leaderboard table renders without horizontal overflow
    And the leaderboard table shows a row with my nickname, time, and attempt count

    When I tap "游戏"
    Then the URL path is /
